org.wikidata.wdtk.storage.dbquery

Interface TrieIterator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TripleTrieIterator

    public interface TrieIterator
    Interface to iterate over a trie. The position of the iterator is a node in the tree structure. The regular iterator operations iterate sideways over the siblings of this node. Two additional operations can be used to descend to the first child of the current node or to move back up to the parent.
    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch

    • Method Detail

      • getLevel

        int getLevel()
        Return the current level in the tree. The first level is 1. The root of the trie structure (level 0) does not contain data and cannot be selected with the iterator.
        Returns:
        the current level of the iteration

      • getKey

        int getKey()
        Returns the key at the current position. This is equivalent to calling getKey(int) with the result of getLevel().
        Returns:
        key at current iterator position

      • getKey

        int getKey(int level)
        Returns the key at the current position in the specified level. The level must be smaller or equal to the current level.
        Parameters:
        level - the level of which to get the key
        Returns:
        key at current iterator position at the given level

      • next

        void next()
        Advances the iterator by one. This must only be called if hasNext() returns true.

        Returns:
